1) Diplomacy
Diplomacy is the art and science of maintaining peaceful
relationships between nations, groups, or individuals.
Often, diplomacy refers to representatives of different groups
discussing such issues as conflict, trade, the environment,
technology, or security. People who practice diplomacy are called
diplomats.
