In other words, liberal political economists believe that by
removing barriers to the free movement of goods and services
among countries, as well as within them, countries would be
encouraged to specialize in producing certain goods, thereby
contributing to the optimum utilization of resources such as land,
labor, capital, and entrepreneurial ability worldwide.
If countries focused on what they do best and freely trade their
goods with each other,all of them would benefit. The concept that
captures this idea is also known as comparative advantage.
