2) Structuralism
Structuralism : is a variant of the Marxist perspective and starts
analysis from a practical diagnosis of the specific structural problems
of the international liberal capitalist economic system whose main
feature is centre-periphery (dependency) relationship between the
Global North and the Global South which permanently resulted in an
unequal (trade and investment) exchange.Structuralism ሌላኛው የ Marxism theory ነው ፤ ተመሳሳይ ናቸው በፅንሰ
